n  from nbgs inception until the establishment of the bank of greece in  nbg enjoyed the right to issue banknotes when the athens stock exchange was founded in  nbg immediately listed on the exchange a listing it has retained to the present the bank is currently listed on the athens exchange athex ete isin grs it is a constituent of the ftseathex large cap index from  to  it was listed on the new york stock exchange nysenbg adr isin us contents  history  post wwii  s and after  branches  major acquisitions  notable persons in the history of the nbg  patronage and sponsorship  see also  notes  further reading  external links historyedit this section needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed march  learn how and when to remove this template message jeangabriel eynard georgios stavrou julius von hößlinέσσλιν nbg was founded in  in athens by the decree on national bank recommendation official gazette no  of march   p  according to which the national bank is a private limited company based in athens with a capital of  drachmas divided into  shares of  drachmas at its founding the major shareholder of the national bank was the greek state with  shares out of  other major shareholders were nicholas zosimas with  shares jeangabriel eynard with  shares king louis of bavaria with  shares konstantinos vranis with  shares adolf graf with  shares and theodoros rallis with  shares rothshild frères paris bought  shares and jeangabriel eynard bought another  shares in their name to boost the prestige of the new bank it used to have the sole right of note issue which it lost in  when the newly established bank of greece took over as the countrys central bank in  nbg acquired the privileged bank of epirus and thessaly pronomiouchos trapeza epirothessalias andreas syngros had founded the bank in volos in  unfortunately the bank was unable to recover from his death and from the grecoturkish war  royal decree on the foundation of the national bank of greece  april  stock issue of  the headquarters in athens the arrival of the th century saw nbg begin its international expansion in  nbg established banque d’orient together with nationalbank für deutschland which almost immediately withdrew from the venture the greeks kept the branches in thessaloniki smyrna and alexandria three years later nbg chose cyprus as the location for its first branch outside greece nbg became governmentowned during the first world war when nbg refused to finance new military equipment for the greek government the government then passed a law that permitted the government to appoint its own people to the banks board in  nbg acquired the bank of crete trapeza kritis however in  the treaty of lausanne provided for a compulsory exchange of populations between greece and turkey leading to the departure of the greeks from smyrna as a result banque d’orient closed its branch there the s saw further international expansion in  nbg and bank of athens combined their activities in egypt into a joint subsidiary banque nationale de grèce et d’athènes two years later nbg acquired banque dorient trapeza anatolis then in  on the eve of the second world war the nbg established a subsidiary in new york city the hellenic bank trust company in world war ii the nbg in greece was managed by deutsche bank for the german occupiers post wwiiedit economy of greece overview agriculture bank of greece companies shipping stock exchange companies listed tourism greece topics culture education geography history politics greece portal v t e in  the nbg took over the bank of athens which was at that time the second largest bank in greece both banks cooperated before in their foreign branches in middle east which were operated as banque nationale de grèce et d’athènes the nbg took over also the affiliated south african bank of athens est  which nbg still owns the former headquarters o